Humans have degenerated quite a bit. Foragers needed to have a good understanding about
tools for hunting, building a house, making food with scarce resources, preparing for the
change of seasons, ... We as humans have a tremendous capacity for learning new things rather
quickly. When the modern marketplace was introduced, things changed a lot. People specialized
in an area, which was necessary because competition got higher and higher. You needed to pick
a field which was in high demand and then master that field. 
